text:
263-65 Vanderbilt Avenue, east side, between Willoughby and Dekalb Avenues. The real estate atlases from 1886 to 1918 show this to be horse stables, located just south of the old Charles Pratt Mansion. Note the horse weather vane atop the building.
View 2 is south along the avenue.

P. L. Sperr

View 1: July 22, 1934
View 2: October 12, 1940
